--  Generic Bridge Validation — Retroactive Consistency Tests
-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
--  This module verifies that every existing bridge instance in the
--  repository can be expressed as an instantiation of the generic
--  bridge machinery from  Bridge/GenericBridge.agda .
--
--  For each concrete bridge, we:
--
--    1. Construct a  PatchData  (or  OrbitReducedPatch ) from the
--       existing observable functions and agreement paths.
--
--    2. Apply  GenericEnriched  (or  orbit-bridge-witness ) to
--       extract a fully proof-carrying  BridgeWitness .
--
--    3. Verify coherence: the generic construction's observable
--       functions agree definitionally with the concrete ones.
--
--  The fact that this module TYPE-CHECKS is the validation:
--  it proves that the generic architecture subsumes all existing
--  bridges without modifying any of them.
--
--  Instances validated:
--
--    §1. Star       (10 regions, 2D {5,4} star)         — PatchData
--    §2. Filled     (90 regions, 2D {5,4} disk)         — PatchData
--    §3. Honeycomb  (26 regions, 3D {4,3,5} BFS star)   — PatchData
--    §4. Dense-50   (139 regions, 3D {4,3,5} dense)     — PatchData
--    §5. Dense-100  (717 regions → 8 orbits)            — OrbitReducedPatch
--    §6. Dense-200  (1246 regions → 9 orbits)           — OrbitReducedPatch
--
--  Reference:
--    docs/10-frontier.md §5.5   (What This Achieves)
--    docs/10-frontier.md §5.11  (Phase C.0 — item 2: retroactive validation)
--    docs/10-frontier.md §5.12  (Conditions for Advancement — item 1)
--
--  Condition for advancement (§5.12):
